This paper is about a new deep convolutional neural network architecture that achieves high performance on image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the behavior and performance of the network, which suggests that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions a new path-wise training procedure, which could be relevant to sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
